WEBVTT



00:00:09.952 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.952 --> 00:00:25.984
Thanks for tuning back in. on today's episode, we're excited to have Joe Mazziata reading Psalm 142 as part of our Psalms Project journey.

00:00:30.720 --> 00:00:32.800
Hi, I'm Joe Mazziata.

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:35.872
Please join me in reading Psalm 142.

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:41.536
With my voice I cry out to the Lord.

00:00:41.664 --> 00:00:44.960
With my voice I plead for mercy to the Lord.

00:00:45.344 --> 00:00:47.936
I pour out my complaint before him.

00:00:47.776 --> 00:00:49.920
I tell my trouble before him.

00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:53.824
When my spirit faints within me, you know my way.

00:00:54.048 --> 00:00:56.000
in the path where I walk.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:58.848
They're hidden in a trap for me.

00:00:59.104 --> 00:01:01.056
Look to the right and see.

00:01:01.088 --> 00:01:02.944
There is none.

00:01:02.784 --> 00:01:04.672
Who takes notice of me.

00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:07.232
No refuge remains to me.

00:01:07.232 --> 00:01:09.376
No one cares for my soul.

00:01:09.888 --> 00:01:11.904
I cry to you, O Lord.

00:01:11.776 --> 00:01:13.024
I say,

00:01:12.896 --> 00:01:15.328
You are my refuge.

00:01:15.392 --> 00:01:18.400
My portion in the land of the living.

00:01:18.784 --> 00:01:20.640
Attend to my cry.

00:01:20.896 --> 00:01:23.136
For I am brought very low.

00:01:23.584 --> 00:01:26.272
Deliver me from my persecutors.

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:28.128
For they are too strong for me.

00:01:28.736 --> 00:01:30.880
Bring me out of prison.

00:01:30.912 --> 00:01:32.672
that I may give thanks.

00:01:34.496 --> 00:01:35.840
To your name.

00:01:36.672 --> 00:01:38.016
The righteous

00:01:37.824 --> 00:01:39.296
Will surround me.

00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:43.136
For you will deal bountifully with me.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:48.704
As i read through psalms 142

00:01:48.704 --> 00:01:50.880
A couple things stood out to me.

00:01:51.296 --> 00:01:56.064
As I recall, this was a period where David was being chased.

00:01:55.968 --> 00:01:57.504
He actually was

00:01:57.440 --> 00:01:59.296
Held up in a cave

00:01:59.168 --> 00:02:00.928
with his armies.

00:02:00.832 --> 00:02:02.560
Greatly outnumbered,

00:02:02.336 --> 00:02:03.328
And,

00:02:03.232 --> 00:02:05.728
and outmanned

00:02:05.408 --> 00:02:07.488
And truly trapped.

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:11.680
This is a time where David's pleading

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:15.488
The first thing I noticed, however, is that David had

00:02:15.712 --> 00:02:18.112
Seems to be in a real

00:02:18.272 --> 00:02:20.032
Self-centered mode

00:02:20.032 --> 00:02:21.728
It's all about him.

00:02:22.144 --> 00:02:25.472
Nobody likes him, almost a pity party.

00:02:26.304 --> 00:02:28.896
The fact that he has 600 of his

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:33.312
Faithful troops with them doesn't play into this story. it's all about him.

00:02:34.016 --> 00:02:38.368
I'm bothered by that a little bit. I'm also bothered by the fact that he

00:02:38.144 --> 00:02:40.960
seems to be pleading to Jesus.

00:02:40.864 --> 00:02:42.464
and God for

00:02:42.848 --> 00:02:47.744
Relief from this this strain and get him out of this situation

00:02:47.424 --> 00:02:53.632
And he's putting conditions on his praise for the Lord. If you get me out of this,

00:02:53.984 --> 00:02:56.800
fix, I will then praise you.

00:02:56.768 --> 00:02:57.888
and.

00:02:59.392 --> 00:03:05.056
that bothers me as well I've always felt that you know the Lord isn't one to

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:08.256
To be put in, given any conditional love.

00:03:08.192 --> 00:03:14.112
You should praise them whether things are going well and when things are going poorly as well.

00:03:14.496 --> 00:03:23.392
I think that we all have done this and we continue to do this. This is an example of how Psalms

00:03:23.232 --> 00:03:27.296
Really is about real people going through real emotions.

00:03:27.008 --> 00:03:30.144
And even those that we look to

00:03:30.016 --> 00:03:38.336
in history as great people such as David had the same emotions that we all go through on a regular basis now.

00:03:46.880 --> 00:03:55.008
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:03:55.072 --> 00:04:04.576
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast. Thank you.
